@flexiarg budgeted-action-selection/mana-gated-work
@title Mana-Gated Work: action selection bounded by available budget
@sigils [💰/可]
@keywords mana, budget, license, action-selection, gating, dana, sospeso
@audience action selectors, agent dispatch implementers, mission-control operators
@tone analytic-foundational
@factor Wise-restraint (saṁyama) — selecting only what budget allows
@style pattern
@references [structure/mana-allostasis structure/block-as-futonic-revolution invariant-coherence/drain-channel-shape p4ng/agent-as-mana-unit-was-the-wrong-unit]
@references-extra ["`structure/mana-allostasis` describes the *balance dynamic*" "(the integral of awards − drains over time). This pattern" "describes the *gate dynamic* (the live decision rule that" "consults the balance). Together they form the action-selection" "contract: select what you can afford to act on, and act in a" "way that closes the block before the next selection. Both" "voices, harmolodic."]

! conclusion: 
  Action selection should be constrained by available budget or
  license, not by priority alone. A proposed action is *gated* —
  permitted to run — only when the operator's session-level mana
  balance can sustain its expected cost. Block-closure at hinges
  awards mana; allostatic-load drains it; the gate is the live
  intersection of "what does this action cost" and "what does the
  session have to spend." Without the gate, priority sorting alone
  recommends everything that is locally desirable, regardless of
  whether the substrate can sustain its execution. With the gate,
  the system selects within a budget the operator's metabolic state
  can actually afford.

  + context:
    The candidate invariant `mana-gated-work` was named in the
    futon5a stack-stereolithography queue (`run-064`,
    `F-budgeted-action-selection`) with the summary: "Action
    selection should be constrained by available budget or license,
    not by priority alone. Some proposed work should be selectable
    only when enough budget is available, but this remains weakly
    implemented." The mission `M-bounded-in-flight-state` formalises
    the *balance dynamic* (`structure/mana-allostasis`) the gate
    operates on; this pattern names the gate itself.

    Production precedent: `futon5/scripts/nonstarter_mana.clj`'s
    `sospeso` command computes `(1-p)*C` to pool as pure *dana*
    (Buddhist generosity) when an action of cost C is committed at
    confidence p. The pool IS the session-level budget; the
    confidence-weighted cost IS the gating signal.

  + IF:
    The system is selecting which proposed action to run from a
    queue (the priority queue, the mission queue, the agent
    backpack, etc.), and the actions vary in cost.

  + HOWEVER:
    Pure priority-sorted selection has no metabolic awareness:
      - High-priority but high-cost actions can be selected even
        when the session's mana balance is depleted, accelerating
        substrate corruption.
      - Low-priority but low-cost actions that would maintain
        balance never get a turn because higher-priority items
        always exist.
      - The operator's felt fatigue has no path into the action-
        selection loop.

    + ANTI-PATTERNS:
      - **Priority-only selection** (no gate): the default broken
        state this pattern names.
      - **Hard-cap-only selection** (no priority): everything below
        a threshold runs in arbitrary order; misses important work.
      - **Per-agent budgets** (precursor): see
        `p4ng/agent-as-mana-unit-was-the-wrong-unit`.
      - **Counterfeit gate-pass**: action declares its cost as
        lower than it actually is to slip through. Mitigated by
        cost-confidence weighting (sospeso) and post-hoc
        reconciliation against actual block-closure cost.

  + THEN:
    Gate the selector: a candidate action runs if and only if the
    session's current mana balance can afford its expected cost.
    Define cost in terms of the channels of `mana-allostasis`:
    working-tree pressure increment, mission-proliferation increment,
    session-sprawl increment, untriaged-evidence increment. Define
    *afford* in terms of the session's running balance + a small
    safety margin. Reject (with `:reason :insufficient-budget`)
    rather than execute when the gate fails.

    Selection becomes a two-step process:
      1. Priority sort the candidate set.
      2. Walk the sorted list; for each candidate, ask the gate
         "can the session afford this?" Take the first that
         passes; defer the rest with explicit reason.

    + DIAGNOSTIC:
      - Selector consistently rejects high-priority items: budget
        is depleted at session level. Operator should close
        blocks (any drain channel) before continuing.
      - Selector consistently accepts everything: gate may not be
        wired, or budget thresholds may be too generous. Recheck
        cost-quantum estimates.
      - Selector accepts one action then immediately rejects the
        next at apparently equal cost: stochastic gate behaviour
        points at miscalibrated confidence in the cost estimator.

    + ON-DANA-AS-COST:
      The `nonstarter_mana.clj` precursor's *sospeso → dana* pattern
      is operationally sound. An action committed at confidence p
      with cost C *gives* `(1-p)*C` to the pool — confidence-
      discounted cost is the right cost-quantum because low-confidence
      actions burn budget proportionally more even when they
      succeed. Dana (generosity) is the right metaphor: an action's
      cost is given to the future operator who will close the
      eventual block. The session that takes on cost is the session
      that owes the closure.

    + ON-UNIT-CORRECTION:
      Action-selection budgets attach to sessions, not to agents.
      See `p4ng/agent-as-mana-unit-was-the-wrong-unit` for the
      precursor reasoning. An agent has no metabolism beyond its
      turn; the session is the temporal frame in which budgets
      integrate. A multi-agent session pools its mana economy at
      the session level, not partitioned per-agent.

    + REFERENCES:
      - structure/mana-allostasis — the balance dynamic the gate consults.
      - structure/block-as-futonic-revolution — the unit whose closure replenishes the budget.
      - invariant-coherence/drain-channel-shape — the per-channel cost estimators feed the gate.
      - p4ng/agent-as-mana-unit-was-the-wrong-unit — the precursor unit-error this pattern corrects.
      - futon5a/holes/stack-stereolithography-runs/run-064-budgeted-action-selection--mana-gated-work.md — the candidate invariant in the queue this pattern formalises.
      - futon5/scripts/nonstarter_mana.clj — the production-code precursor.

  + BECAUSE:
    Priority captures what matters in the abstract; budget captures
    what the system can actually sustain right now. Both readings
    are needed. A priority-only selector is a recipe for substrate
    corruption (the operator runs out of capacity to close blocks
    faster than load accumulates). A budget-only selector is a
    recipe for stagnation (high-priority work never gets selected
    because something cheaper always squeezes in). The gate
    composes them.
